Note:
Runa Standard Library: Blockchain Oracle Protocol Module

Provides comprehensive oracle protocol implementation for connecting blockchain systems
with external data sources and real-world information. Implements enterprise-grade
oracle mechanisms including data feeds, price oracles, computation oracles, and
decentralized oracle networks. Competitive with production oracle implementations
in Chainlink, Band Protocol, and other leading oracle service providers.

Features:
- Decentralized oracle networks with consensus mechanisms
- Price feed oracles with aggregation and validation
- Computation oracles for off-chain processing
- Cross-chain data relay and verification
- Oracle reputation systems and stake-based security
- Data source verification and authenticity proofs
- Time-series data aggregation and historical queries
- Real-time event monitoring and trigger systems
- Economic incentive mechanisms for oracle operators
- Dispute resolution and slashing for malicious behavior
- Privacy-preserving oracles with cryptographic commitments
- Oracle service level agreements and uptime guarantees
- Data quality assurance and outlier detection
- Multi-signature verification for critical data
- Oracle marketplace and service discovery
:End Note

Note: Core Oracle Types
Type called "OracleNetwork":
    network_config as OracleNetworkConfiguration
    oracle_registry as OracleRegistry
    data_feed_manager as DataFeedManager
    consensus_engine as ConsensusEngine
    reputation_system as ReputationSystem
    economic_model as EconomicModel
    security_manager as SecurityManager
    dispute_resolver as DisputeResolver
    verification_system as VerificationSystem
    aggregation_engine as AggregationEngine

Type called "OracleNetworkConfiguration":
    network_name as String
    consensus_threshold as Float
    minimum_oracles as Integer
    maximum_oracles as Integer
    stake_requirement as Integer
    slashing_conditions as List[SlashingCondition]
    data_freshness_requirements as DataFreshnessRequirements
    economic_parameters as EconomicParameters

Type called "OracleRegistry":
    registered_oracles as Dictionary[String, Oracle]
    oracle_metadata as Dictionary[String, OracleMetadata]
    service_agreements as Dictionary[String, ServiceAgreement]
    oracle_performance_metrics as Dictionary[String, PerformanceMetrics]

Type called "Oracle":
    oracle_id as String
    oracle_address as String
    oracle_type as OracleType
    operator as String
    stake_amount as Integer
    reputation_score as Float
    data_sources as List[DataSource]
    supported_feeds as List[String]
    service_level_agreement as ServiceLevelAgreement
    status as OracleStatus

Type OracleType is:
    | PRICE_ORACLE
    | COMPUTATION_ORACLE
    | EVENT_ORACLE
    | CROSS_CHAIN_ORACLE
    | WEATHER_ORACLE
    | SPORTS_ORACLE
    | IDENTITY_ORACLE
    | IOT_ORACLE

Type OracleStatus is:
    | ACTIVE
    | INACTIVE
    | SUSPENDED
    | SLASHED
    | UNDER_DISPUTE

Type called "DataFeedManager":
    active_feeds as Dictionary[String, DataFeed]
    feed_specifications as Dictionary[String, FeedSpecification]
    aggregation_jobs as Dictionary[String, AggregationJob]
    historical_data as Dictionary[String, TimeSeriesData]

Type called "DataFeed":
